definitions.definition: One who decides which programs will be shown on a television station , or which songs will be played on a radio station .
A device that installs or controls a software program in some other machine.
A short film feature as part of a longer film program.

main_definition: ( computing ) One who writes computer programs .
secondary_definitions: ( radio , television ) One who decides which programs will be shown on a television station , or which songs will be played on a radio station .
A device that installs or controls a software program in some other machine.
( now rare ) A short film feature as part of a longer film program.
